description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a difference? Something that will challenge and reward you at the same time? To be part of a team that will help motivate and support you? Good, because we think that YOU are exactly what we are looking for! MAU have a position that is calling all Caring and Compassionate Nurses to join our supportive multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This permanent position is well suited to individuals looking to gain skills and experience in the acute setting .They will gain hands on experience in a thriving and supportive workplace, provide high quality care to our patient group while working with a dedicated team of staff who are devoted to improve the quality of care and enhance patients experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be involved with the planning , implementing and monitoring of care of acutely ill patients with an expected length of stay up to 72 hours. They will work collaboratively with the multi disciplinary team and provide safe and seamless discharge planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a comprehensive preceptorship for newly qualified staff and have opportunities for all staff to learn and to develop their nursing skills to support patients admitted with acute and complex medical conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the many other benefits of working at Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, you may also be entitled to apply for our relocation package. As a Trust we recognise the importance of securing the right candidate for a role; and we therefore offer an attractive relocation package of £1,500 for any nurse relocating more than one hour away from their current address.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
